9 An Act relating to criminal procedure; amending 22
O.S. 2021, Sections 1175.1, as last amended by
10 Section 1, Chapter 364, O.S.L. 2025, 1175.3, as
amended by Section 2, Chapter 73, O.S.L. 2024,
11 1175.4, as amended by Section 3, Chapter 73, O.S.L.
2024, 1175.6b, as amended by Section 4, Chapter 73,
12 O.S.L. 2024, 1175.7 and 1175.8 (22 O.S. Supp. 2025,
Sections 1175.1, 1175.3, 1175.4 and 1175.6b), which
13 relate to competency determinations; updating name of
forensic examiners; providing for evaluations of
14 individuals rather than examinations; directing
courts to appoint medical supervisors under certain
15 circumstances; providing for inpatient or outpatient
care; requiring medical supervisors to provide
16 periodic reports of progress; authorizing the payment
of medical supervisor services from court funds;
17 providing procedures for determining appropriate
treatment for persons found incompetent and committed
18 to the Department of Mental Health and Substance
Abuse Services; requiring individuals to consent and
19 comply with certain terms and conditions when
participating in community-based outpatient
20 competency restoration programs; directing providers
to submit reports concerning compliance or
21 violations; allowing modification of court orders
under certain circumstances; providing for inpatient
22 care when necessary; authorizing participating
individuals to receive additional treatment or
23 support services; prohibiting courts from committing
persons who are currently serving active sentences;
24 providing an exception; making provisions applicable
Req. No. 16023 Page 1

1 regardless of when criminal sentencing occurred;
providing conflict of laws provision; providing for
2 the appointment of medical supervisors under certain
circumstances; allowing for inpatient or outpatient
3 treatment; requiring periodic progress reports to the
court; authorizing payment of services from court
4 funds; permitting the use of private treatment
facilities; directing courts to conduct additional
5 competency hearings within certain number of days
after receiving reports of competency; and providing
6 an effective date.
